crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This binary is a downloader that establishes persistence. It creates a LaunchAgent plist at `/Library/LaunchAgents/com.zoom.plist` to execute a payload from `/var/tmp/logd`. It then downloads this payload from `https://zoom[.]callservice[.]us`, makes it executable (`chmod 777`), and runs it using `_system`. Persistence is activated using `launchctl load`. The use of names like 'zoom' and 'logd' is a clear attempt at masquerading.
